Gonin Gora community in the outskirt of Kaduna metropolis has commended Governor Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai for the road construction works in the area. Speaking during a press briefing, the Village Head, Chief John Dodo Yusuf Sarki while commending Governor El-Rufai said, previous governments in the state made several promises to the community, which were not fulfilled. “We are very happy today that, Governor Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai has turned Gonin Gora to Small London. Anyone that came to our community in the recent past and comes back today will see that, development has come to Gonin Gora. “Governments in the past have made series of promises to us without fulfilling them. But today, under the government of Malam Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai, we now have roads. “As part of measures to show our appreciation to the government, we have put in place measures to maintain the roads. We have carried out enlightenment programme and told our people to preserve the road by avoiding dumping refuse in the drainage.” The village head also appealed to the Governor to upgrade the community’s Primary Healthcare Centre (PHC) to a General Hospital, saying such will enable the hospital take care of the health needs of the ever expanding community. Also, the Chief Imam of the community, Sheikh Suleiman Ahmad said, the community has prioritized promotion of peaceful coexistence among the people through religious engagement.  Demolition threat: Gonin-Gora residents are peace lovers - community Demolition: We’re peace-loving, Gonin-Gora residents tell El-Rufai Auto crashes: Gonin-Gora residents accuse gov’t of neglect OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY